        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "perf(memory): batch memory embeddings across files",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Batch-enabled source-wide embedding now defers memory and session source indexing into one shared queue before submitting provider batches.\n- OpenAI-compatible source-wide verbose logs now print the batching path, source distribution, file count, chunk count, group, and flush reason.\n- The regression test now requires forced memory+session indexing to use one provider runtime batch instead of separate per-source batches.\n- Merged current `origin/main` and resolved the `packages/memory-host-sdk/src/host/batch-runner.ts` conflict while keeping safe poll interval clamping plus batch wait/debug forwarding.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior or issue addressed:** `openclaw memory index --force --verbose` should not submit separate OpenAI-compatible embedding batches for memory files and session files when both sources are enabled; the verbose output should also identify the source-wide batching path.\n- **Real environment tested:** Real OpenClaw CLI from `/media/vdc/code/ai/aispace/openclaw-worktrees/pr-88238`, isolated `OPENCLAW_HOME`, 3 memory markdown files, 2 session transcript files, provider `openai`, model `test-embed`, batch enabled, local OpenAI-compatible batch HTTP endpoint on `127.0.0.1:18083`.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n\n```bash\ncd /media/vdc/code/ai/aispace/openclaw-worktrees/pr-88238\nOPENCLAW_HOME=/media/vdc/code/ai/aispace/openclaw-pr-88238-evidence/runtime-home \\\nNO_COLOR=1 \\\npnpm openclaw memory index --force --verbose \\\n  > /media/vdc/code/ai/aispace/openclaw-pr-88238-evidence/openclaw-memory-index.log 2>&1\n```\n\n- **Evidence after fix:**\n\n```text\nMemory Index (main)\nSources: memory (MEMORY.md + $OPENCLAW_HOME/workspace/memory/*.md), sessions ($OPENCLAW_HOME/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/*.jsonl)\n[memory] embeddings: source-wide batch prepare files=5 sources=memory=3,sessions=2 maxFiles=1024 maxChunks=4096\n[memory] embeddings: source-wide batch submit group=1 source=memory+sessions files=5 chunks=5 sources=memory=3,sessions=2 reason=end\n[memory] embeddings: openai batch submit\n[memory] embeddings: openai batch created\nMemory index updated (main).\n```\n\n```json\n{\n  \"uploads\": [\n    {\n      \"fileId\": \"file-1\",\n      \"requests\": 5,\n      \"inputs\": [\n        \"# Log\\nAlpha memory line.\\nZebra memory line.\\n\",\n        \"# Log\\nBeta memory line.\\n\",\n        \"# Log\\nGamma memory line.\\n\",\n        \"User: Session alpha memory line.\",\n        \"Assistant: Session beta memory line.\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"batches\": [\n    {\n      \"batchId\": \"batch-1\",\n      \"inputFileId\": \"file-1\",\n      \"outputFileId\": \"output-1\",\n      \"requests\": 5\n    }\n  ],\n  \"statusPolls\": [],\n  \"outputReads\": [\n    \"output-1\"\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n- **Observed result after fix:** One OpenAI-compatible batch was created with 5 requests spanning both configured sources: 3 memory files and 2 session transcript files. The console output now makes the source-wide code path and source distribution visible.\n- **What was not tested:** A live third-party embedding endpoint was not tested because this environment has no embedding base URL/API key/model variables. The real OpenClaw CLI and OpenAI-compatible provider path were tested against a local OpenAI-compatible batch endpoint.\n- **Target test file:** `extensions/memory-core/src/memory/index.test.ts`\n\n## Regression Test Plan\n\n```text\nOPENCLAW_TEST_MEMORY_UNSAFE_REINDEX=1 node scripts/test-projects.mjs extensions/memory-core/src/memory/index.test.ts src/plugins/openai-compatible-embedding-provider.test.ts extensions/memory-core/src/memory/generic-embedding-provider.bridge.test.ts\n[test] passed 2 Vitest shards in 33.76s\n\nOPENCLAW_TEST_MEMORY_UNSAFE_REINDEX=1 node scripts/test-projects.mjs extensions/memory-core/src/memory/index.test.ts src/plugins/openai-compatible-embedding-provider.test.ts extensions/memory-core/src/memory/generic-embedding-provider.bridge.test.ts packages/memory-host-sdk/src/host/batch-runner.test.ts\n[test] passed 3 Vitest shards in 69.04s\n\ngit diff --name-only --diff-filter=U\n(no output)\n\ngit diff --check -- packages/memory-host-sdk/src/host/batch-runner.ts extensions/memory-core/src/memory/manager-sync-ops.ts extensions/memory-core/src/memory/manager-embedding-ops.ts extensions/memory-core/src/memory/index.test.ts\n(no output)\n\npnpm tsgo:test:extensions\nexit code 0\n```\n\n## Root Cause\n\n- **Root cause:** The previous source-wide path still indexed memory files and session files through separate source sync calls. That made the OpenAI-compatible provider submit separate batches per source, and the verbose output did not expose enough source-wide batching details to distinguish that path from per-file or per-source batching.\n",
